                <ul>
                    <li>Most users were using a google sheet or similar, or avo, to track events, and both solutions required a lot of integration headache with their warehouse</li>
                    <li>Rudderstack's advantage was our place in the pipeline due to automation potential</li>
                    <li>DevOps engineers are RS core users, and wanted credibility</li>
                    <li>Marketers and business users (secondary) wanted visibility</li>
                    <li>The solution had to accommodate API/automated import and hand-create, with automated prioritized to users</li>
                    <li>Tracking plans and data catalog should be two separate and distinct features</li>
                    </ul>
