                <h2>Solutions</h2>
                <h3>Data Catalog</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Separated from tracking plans completely - this big architecture decision that would pay off later and in other features</li>
                    <li>Events, which are usually represented as code strings, were broken into name, description, and type for easy filtering. Categories are not tied to the codebase and provide another layer of organization for different teams, which was a request for business users</li>
                    <li>Tabbed structure provides credibility that the audit API is functional as well as organization by default for often automated or unwieldy data flows</li>
                </ul>
                <div class="image-placeholder">
