                <h3>Designing for developers</h3>
                <p>A common challenge at Rudderstack was using code functionality-as-requirements, in this case, custom rules that can be applied to properties.</p>
                <p>I had daily calls with engineering to understand what needed to be reflected in the UI and collaborate on the highly complex data formats and functionality.</p>
                <p>My solution was a flyout attached to the property at all times, wherever it manifests in the Rudderstack UI.</p>
